"Smith S.J., Wigley T.M.L.","Global Warming Potentials: 2. Accuracy",2000,"Climatic Change","44","4",,"459","469",,,10.1023/A:1005537014987,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0033962587&partnerID=40&md5=18b69547faaa4162c77173826840dcd3","Climate and Global Dynamics Division, Natl. Ctr. for Atmospheric Research, P.O. Box 3000, Boulder, CO 80307-3000, United States","Smith, S.J., Climate and Global Dynamics Division, Natl. Ctr. for Atmospheric Research, P.O. Box 3000, Boulder, CO 80307-3000, United States; Wigley, T.M.L., Climate and Global Dynamics Division, Natl. Ctr. for Atmospheric Research, P.O. Box 3000, Boulder, CO 80307-3000, United States","This paper exposes flaws in the mathematical structure of the Global Warming Potential (GWP) concept. These lead to errors when emissions changes in different greenhouse gases are compared. The most fundamental problem is that the unit impulse response functions from which GWPs, and many of their proposed alternatives, are constructed provide an incomplete representation of the relationship between emissions and radiative forcing. Additional errors occur when GWPs are used to compare finite-length emissions changes.",,"accuracy assessment; climate change; forecasting method; global warming",,,,,,"Albritton, D.L., Derwent, R.G., Isaksen, I.S.A., Lal, M., Wuebbles, D.J., Trace Gas Radiative Forcing Indices (1995) Climate Change 1994: Radiative Forcing of Climate Change and an Evaluation of the IPCC IS92 Emissions Scenarios, pp. 205-231. , Houghton, J. T., Meira Filho, L. G., Bruce, J., Lee, H., Callander, B. A., Haites, E., Harris, N., and Maskell, K. (eds.), Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, U.K; Caldeira, K., Kasting, J.F., Insensitivity of Global Warming Potentials to Carbon Dioxide Emission Scenarios (1993) Nature, 366, pp. 251-253; Harvey, L.D.D., A Guide to Global Warming Potentials (GWPs) (1993) Energy Pol., 21, pp. 24-34; Lashof, D.A., Ahuja, D.R., Relative Contributions of Greenhouse Gas Emissi